Package dev.nicklasw.bankid.client.model

Class PhoneRequirement

java.lang.Object
dev.nicklasw.bankid.client.model.PhoneRequirement
public final class PhoneRequirement extends Object
RP may use the requirement parameter to describe how a signature must be created and verified. A typical use case is to require Mobile BankID or a certain card reader. A requirement can be set for both auth and sign orders.

    • getPinCode

      public Boolean getPinCode()
      Users are required to sign the transaction with their PIN code, even if they have biometrics activated.

    • getCardReader

      public CardReader getCardReader()
      "class1" (default) – The transaction must be performed using a card reader where the PIN code is entered on a computer keyboard, or a card reader of higher class.

      "class2" – The transaction must be performed using a card reader where the PIN code is entered on the reader, or a reader of higher class.

      "no value" – defaults to "class1". This condition should be combined with a certificatePolicies for a smart card to avoid undefined behaviour.

    • getCertificatePolicies

      public String getCertificatePolicies()
      The oid in certificate policies in the user certificate. List of String. One wildcard "" is allowed from position 5 and forward i.e. 1.2.752.78.
